Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C.

Thinly slice the @Portobello Mushrooms{2}. Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large #frying pan{} on high heat. Add the mushrooms and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring often, until browned, ~{6-8%minutes}.

> TIP: Add a splash of oil to the pan if needed.

Once the mushrooms are cooked, stir in the garlic and fry for ~{1%minute}.

While the mushrooms are cooking, drain the @Mozzarella{1} and pat dry with #kitchen paper{}, making sure you squeeze out as much liquid as possible. Then tear it into pieces.

Halve the @Baby Plum Tomatoes{125}.

In a #small bowl{}, combine the @Fresh Pesto{50} and @Olive Oil for the Pesto{1.5%tbsp}, then set aside.

Pop the @Plain Naans{2} onto a large #baking tray{}.

Spread the pesto mixture evenly all over the base of each naan, leaving a 1cm border around the edge.

Lay the garlicky mushrooms onto the naanizzas.

Scatter over the mozzarella.

When the oven is hot, bake the naanizzas on the top shelf until the cheese is melted and bubbling and the base is crisp, ~{6-8%minutes}.

Meanwhile, pop the @Wild Rocket{40} and baby plum tomatoes into a #bowl{}.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, mix together then set aside.

Once everything is cooked, serve the naanizzas topped with the salad and a drizzle of the @Balsamic Glaze{12}. Enjoy!

> STEP 1 MOD: If you've added bacon lardons to your meal, cook @?British Smoked Bacon Lardons{90} with the mushrooms in the step above. IMPORTANT: Cook bacon thoroughly.